{"title":"Muoverti TiltBike balances, steers, brakes and accelerates to revolutionize indoor cycling","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/04/muoverti-tiltbike-balances-steers-brakes-and-accelerates-to-revolutionize-indoor-cycling/","date":1636048856000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike lean angle riding steering braking pedalling\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-277349\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>The Muoverti TiltBike is a new, immersive stationary indoor training bike for riders who want their at-home workouts to simulate their on-road (<em>and off-road</em>) rides in almost every way. The supposed “real feel” stems from its unique rider-tuned, elastomer-guided lateral frame rotation. The TiltBike is designed to be used as the controller for Zwift, TrainerRoad, and thanks to the steering, tilt, and braking sensors, E-Sports platforms such as Descenders, too. The Muoverti TiltBike is to be exhibited at Rouleur Live this week, but here’s a quick preview of what’s to come in 2022.</p><p><iframe loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"675\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/02lmUi_aVIc?version=3&amp;rel=1&amp;showsearch=0&amp;showinfo=1&amp;iv_load_policy=1&amp;fs=1&amp;hl=en-US&amp;autohide=2&amp;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></p><h2>Muoverti TiltBike</h2><div id=\"attachment_277460\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277460\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike side on view\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1066\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113105/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-pink-leaning-stationary-bike-trainer-zwift-trainerroad-1536x1023.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277460\">A highlight of the TiltBike platform is that you can digitally customize the resistance increments to replicate the groupsets of all leading manufacturers.</p></div><p>While there are numerous indoor trainer platforms that allow the rider to exercise some semblance of on-road balance, we’re unaware of any that are quite so integrated and immersive as the Muoverti TiltBike. Most are merely rocker platforms that you place your indoor trainer on top of; these have a massive footprint and generally take some time to fettle with and set up correctly. The TiltBike is sort of like a standalone trainer and a rocker platform combined, and a heck of a lot more than that too.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike lean control tilt sensor\" width=\"1600\" height=\"2400\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-200x300.jpg 200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-800x1200.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-80x120.jpg 80w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-768x1152.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-1024x1536.jpg 1024w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113101/muoverti-tiltbike-frame-lateral-lean-controller-1365x2048.jpg 1365w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>We don’t have many details as of yet, but it seems the lean angle, and ease with which the bike leans, can be tuned according to the rider’s weight, just as the inflatable balls underneath the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2021/04/21/review-kom-full-motion-rocker-plate-rpv2-rocks-side-to-side-and-front-to-back/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">KOM Full Motion Rocker Plate</a> can be pressure-tuned to the rider’s preferences. The TiltBike is said to use elastomer-guided lateral frame rotation to achieve this, so presumably, it is the elastomer that can be swapped out to tune the lean characteristics.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike cockpit braking steering sensors\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113114/muoverti-tiltbike-steering-sensor-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Irrespective of how that lean characteristic is tuned, the key point here is that tilt data, along with the steering, braking, and of course, pedaling data is integrated to allow the TiltBike to be the controller of your avatar across many different virtual training and E-Sports platforms.</p><div id=\"attachment_277462\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277462\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike lean angle riding steering braking pedalling\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04113111/muoverti-tiltbike-lean-angle-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277462\">Self-centering digitized handlebar steering allows the bike to move freely under the rider when seated or climbing and sprinting out of the saddle</p></div><p>Muoverti says their system uses a dynamic electromagnetic resistance control and physics engine to algorithmically replicate the feeling of physical forces such as rolling resistance, incline, weight, acceleration, braking, and inertia. The algorithms are said to update 1,000 times per second, in constant communication with the resistance control resulting in highly accurate feedback from digital training and riding platforms.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1.jpg\" alt=\"muoverti tiltbike pedaling resistance electromagnetic carbon belt drive silent\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114119/muoverti-tiltbike-in-game-riding-1-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p>Magnetic resistance is connected to the cranks via a carbon belt drive, said to make for a virtually silent riding experience.&nbsp;</p><div id=\"attachment_277472\"><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit.jpg\"><img aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-277472\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit.jpg\" alt=\"muovertitiltbike handlebar mounted joystick controller\" width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit.jpg 1600w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit-800x534.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/04114516/muoverti-tiltbike-mini-joystick-controller-cockpit-1536x1024.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1600px) 100vw, 1600px\"></a></p><p id=\"caption-attachment-277472\">A shifter integrated mini joystick allows the rider to interact with digital platforms without the need to dismount</p></div><p>The TiltBike allows the rider to view ride data including power, speed, cadence, L/R balance, pedal smoothness, torque effectiveness, lateral force, and even seated vs standing readings; all are provided in real-time <em>without</em> any need for additional sensors.</p><p>Of course, fit can be customized to suit riders of differing heights, as well as tuned to a mountain bike, road, or gravel geometry. A traditional quick-release seat post clamp is included for saddle height adjustment, while a standard rail clamp allows riders to install their preferred saddle. The TiltBike gets a patented adjustable stack and reach handlebar, as well as adjustable length cranks. Overall, the adjustability allows for geometry from frame sizes 49 to 64.</p><p>The Muoverti TiltBike is due in 2022, but we have no idea on the price yet! Watch this space.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.muoverti.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Muoverti.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"8f3d40e8961ac0df3a185cf960d7db9ec248f64371722529dad7bd173318a527","category":"Cycling"}